  "prompt": "Who wrote the 2nd amendment?",
  "response": "The Second Amendment to the United States Constitution was drafted by James Madison. Madison is often called the \"Father of the Constitution\" because of his significant role in its drafting and promotion. The Second Amendment was ratified in 1791 as part of the Bill of Rights, the first ten amendments to the Constitution, which were introduced to safeguard individual liberties and address concerns raised during the Constitution's ratification process. While Madison played a pivotal role in drafting these amendments, the ideas and language were influenced by contributions from many others during the debates and discussions that shaped the Bill of Rights.",
